        <!-- categories -->

        <div class="faq-items">
            <ul id="basics" class="faq-group">
                <li class="faq-title"><h2>Basics</h2></li>
                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">Why isn't my player search working?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>TIMER.GG relies on the player being in an active game to initiate proper timers. The match
                            must have started before a search can be made for the target player (at least on the loading
                            screen or later). The player dashboard will not load if you are in champ select.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">Do I have to sign up?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>Nope! TIMER.GG is a full access free application for all of your League of Legends timing
                            needs. Anytime you're in a game, just input your summoner name above, and you'll be taken to
                            the player dashboard. There you have complete access to all the application has to offer,
                            from voice activation, verbal reminders, and much more!</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">I have a sweet idea for you to implement!</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>I'm all about community collaboration. If you have an idea that you think would work well at
                            TIMER.GG, feel free to send it my way at <strong>support@timer.gg</strong> or on the
                            <strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/timergg">/r/timergg</a></strong> subreddit. Who
                            knows, it might just find it's way onto the app in the near future!</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">How can I support the project?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>I am currently running this development solo. I would greatly appreciate if you were to
                            whitelist TIMER.GG on any ad blocking extensions, but hey, I of all people know ads can get
                            a bit pesky. As I don't have much of a means to professionally market the application,
                            telling your friends and fellow summoners about TIMER.GG helps a ton! For the few generous
                            internet goers with an extra buck to spare, you can also donate to the development <label
                                    for="mySubmit"><strong><a>here</a></strong></label>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>
            </ul>
            <!-- faq-group -->

            <ul id="voice-activation" class="faq-group">
                <li class="faq-title"><h2>Voice Activation</h2></li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">I'm told voice recognition isn't supported by my browser?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>Because voice recognition is relatively new to the modern browser, Chrome is currently the
                            only stable platform for voice recording integration (support for Firefox should be coming
                            very shortly). It may be time to ditch that old browser you've been holding onto for a while
                            <strong>**cough** IE **cough**</strong> and trade it in for a newer model!</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">I don't have a working mic, can I still use the player dashboard?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>Yes, you can! Though voice activation makes controlling the dashboard much easier, all
                            accessible voice commands can be triggered using the dashboard GUI. This includes both
                            objective and player timers, as well as a nifty distortion enchant toggle.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">I have a working mic, but it isn't recording commands?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>When you first enter the player dashboard, a popup window should appear asking for permission
                            to access your microphone. If you accidentally declined the request, or something happened
                            and you weren't sent the request, no worries! Just click the icon in all the way to the
                            right of your URL, as seen in the image below (chrome only).</p>
                        <img style="padding: 10px 300px;" src="../images/index/chrome.png">

                        <p>In the dialogue that opens, make sure to select <strong>"Always allow timer.gg to access your
                                microphone"</strong>. From this window you can also change what mic you wish to record
                            from by selecting it in the drop down menu.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">My mic is connected, but I'm having trouble getting the dashboard to
                        recognize certain champions or other commands.</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>Things like mic quality or the distance you are away from your mic can greatly impact how
                            accurately the dashboard records your voice. So, make sure to speak clearly and make sure
                            you are not too far or too close to your microphone's input.</p>
                        <br>

                        <p>Strong accents or varying phonetic delivery can also lead to poor text-to-speech
                            translations, especially with some of the weird phonetics of some of the champion names. In
                            this case, you can substitute the name of any champion on the dashboard for their respective
                            <strong>Summoner Number</strong>, as seen below.</p>

                        <img style="padding: 10px 300px;" src="../images/index/summonernumber.png">
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

            </ul>
            <!-- faq-group -->

            <ul id="language" class="faq-group">
                <li class="faq-title"><h2>language</h2></li>

                <li>
                    <a class="trigger" href="#0">What languages are supported?</a>

                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p>Currently, the only active language is English. Due to the amount of time it takes to make
                            native language references to the unique champion names and being a solely native English
                            speaker myself, global language integration is not necessarily my highest priority. However,
                            if the application gets enough traction in other regions, I will gladly dedicate the time to
                            setup language references to respective regions.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- faq-content -->
                </li>

            </ul>
            <!-- faq-group -->

        </div>
